Use Case 1: Create a New Task Board

Actor: Student / User
Goal: Create a board to organize tasks
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main flow:
  User clicks 'Create Board'

  User inputs board name, description (optional)

  User selects privacy (private / shared)

  User clicks “Create”

  System saves new board
Postconditions: A new task board is available to the user
Exception: Network failure → board is cached locally and synced later

Use Case 2: Invite Members to Board

Actor: Board Owner / Student
Goal: Invite team members to collaborate
Preconditions: User is logged in, board exists
Main flow:
  User opens board and selects “Invite”

  User enters email/username

  System sends invite notification

  Invite appears on recipient dashboard
Postconditions: Invite pending for target user
Exception: Invalid user → system displays error message

Use Case 3: Accept / Reject Board Invite

Actor: Invited User
Goal: Join or decline shared task board
Preconditions: User received an invitation
Main flow:
  User opens notification/invites panel

  User reviews invite details

  User clicks “Accept” or “Decline”

  System updates board access list
Postconditions: User gains access / invite removed
Exception: Board deleted before response → system shows error

Use Case 4: Mark Task as Complete

Actor: Student
Goal: Update task progress
Preconditions: Task assigned to user or visible to them
Main flow:
  User selects task

  User clicks “Mark as Complete”

  System updates task status and board view

  System awards XP / points / badges (gamified)
Postconditions: Task status updated and rewards granted
Exception: Network failure → completion cached locally

Use Case 5: Earn Rewards (Gamification)

Actor: Student
Goal: Get motivation and track progress
Preconditions: User completes tasks / participates
Main flow:
  User completes tasks or meets milestones

  System calculates XP, badges, streak points

  System updates leaderboard (if enabled)
Postconditions: Gamified stats updated and displayed
Exception: System fails to load leaderboard → stats stored and shown later

Use Case 6: View Shared Task Board

Actor: Student
Goal: See all tasks, assignments, due dates
Preconditions: User has access to board
Main flow:
  User opens board

  System displays tasks, members, due dates, XP badges
Postconditions: User views current board status
Exception: Board load failure → retry message

Use Case 7: Login With Verification

Actor: Student
Goal: Securely access account
Preconditions: Account exists
Main flow:
  User enters email & password

  System checks hashed password

  System sends 2FA code (optional)

  User enters code (if enabled)

  System grants access
Postconditions: User logged in
Exception: Invalid credentials → error message

Use Case 7: Store Password Securely

Actor: System (Stakeholder Requirement)
Goal: Protect user credentials
Preconditions: User registers or changes password
Main flow:
  User submits password

  System hashes password (e.g., bcrypt)

  Store hash in database
Postconditions: Password never stored in plain text
Exception: Hash service fails → deny registration/login

Use Case 8: Fast Task Fetching

Actor: System (Performance Requirement)
Goal: Quickly load user boards and tasks
Preconditions: User requests data
Main flow:
  Backend retrieves data from DB

  Cache frequently accessed boards/tasks

  Return results rapidly
Postconditions: Data delivered quickly
Exception: Cache timeout → fallback to DB fetch